    "TitleKey": "Eckhart_ShipAmbush_E_title",
    "Description": "ECKHART SECURITY, LLC.\nCONTRACTS & DISPATCH\n\nCONTRACT TYPE: Ship Ambush\nAPPROVAL CODE = ~mission(ApprovalCode)\n\nFOR IMMEDIATE PROCESSING\n\nA client of ours has been receiving anonymous threats in an attempt to blackmail them, and after a bit of leg work on our part, we\u2019ve managed to trace it back to an individual who pilots a particular <EM4>~mission(AmbushTarget)</EM4>. The client wants us to take care of this blackmailer before they have a chance to make good. \n\nBased on our assessment, the target shouldn\u2019t be too difficult to handle. They fly by <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4> on the regular, which has an <EM4>emission cloud</EM4> that\u2019s an ideal spot to power down your ship and lie in wait. Sometimes the target is alone but they often travel with other single-seat ships as protection. Best be strategic when you launch your ambush or the <EM4>~mission(AmbushTarget)</EM4> could have a chance to get away. We don\u2019t want to lose this one. We\u2019ll alert other contractors in the area of the ambush so they can come help once it pops off.     \n\nPayment will be issued upon successful completion of contract. The client has also added a bonus payment of <EM4>~mission(ScripAmount) MG Scrip</EM4> for the main contractor.\n\nThis contract is non-negotiable.\n\nThis message may contain confidential, proprietary, privileged and/or private information. The information is intended to be for the use of the individual or entity designated above.",
    "DescriptionKey": "Eckhart_ShipAmbush_E_desc",
    "DisplayDescription": "ECKHART SECURITY, LLC.\nCONTRACTS & DISPATCH\n\nCONTRACT TYPE: Ship Ambush\nAPPROVAL CODE = [ApprovalCode]\n\nFOR IMMEDIATE PROCESSING\n\nA client of ours has been receiving anonymous threats in an attempt to blackmail them, and after a bit of leg work on our part, we\u2019ve managed to trace it back to an individual who pilots a particular <EM4>[AmbushTarget]</EM4>. The client wants us to take care of this blackmailer before they have a chance to make good. \n\nBased on our assessment, the target shouldn\u2019t be too difficult to handle. They fly by <EM4>Asteroid Mining Base</EM4> on the regular, which has an <EM4>emission cloud</EM4> that\u2019s an ideal spot to power down your ship and lie in wait. Sometimes the target is alone but they often travel with other single-seat ships as protection. Best be strategic when you launch your ambush or the <EM4>[AmbushTarget]</EM4> could have a chance to get away. We don\u2019t want to lose this one. We\u2019ll alert other contractors in the area of the ambush so they can come help once it pops off.     \n\nPayment will be issued upon successful completion of contract. The client has also added a bonus payment of <EM4>[ScripAmount] MG Scrip</EM4> for the main contractor.\n\nThis contract is non-negotiable.\n\nThis message may contain confidential, proprietary, privileged and/or private information. The information is intended to be for the use of the individual or entity designated above.",
